1
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:44,680
You're so cute when you smile and laugh.

2
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,120
Do you mean it?

3
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,000
Yes.

4
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:50,200
Mr. Saruj, there is
a big problem in Thailand.

5
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:54,040
Can you return to Thailand?

6
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:56,840
I really can't go back.

7
00:02:57,840 --> 00:03:00,960
Madam Orn can't sponsor me any longer.

8
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,960
I think I'll have to return to Thailand.

9
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:05,640
We'll have half of the world
separating us now.

10
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:08,480
I don't know
when I'll get to see you again.

11
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:12,520
An ambassador who is never in Thailand

12
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,440
and a girl from the country.

13
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:22,640
I'll cherish the good memories
we made together.

14
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:30,840
My goodness.

15
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:33,560
Mobile phones are trending right now.

16
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:36,640
Well, I'm on trend.

17
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:38,200
Can I have your number?

18
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,560
I don't even know how to turn it on.

19
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:44,320
There are so many buttons.

20
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,840
I think holding it is enough.
You look elegant with it.

21
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:47,960
I think so too.

22
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:50,480
I'll carry it
to make myself look chic and all.

23
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:53,600
Chai Lek bought it for me.

24
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:56,840
If you need anything,
just call the home phone number.

25
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:00,080
Okay.

26
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:03,080
- So how's the plan going
- Yes?

27
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:06,840
to match Saruj with Poncheewa?

28
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:09,080
One of them is a workaholic,

29
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:10,880
while all the other does is study.

30
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,640
They're so hard to deal with.

31
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:14,440
Oh dear.

32
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:17,000
Ruj only has one son.

33
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:19,519
If this family's line ends here

34
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,680
without descendants,

35
00:04:21,760 --> 00:04:26,040
how will I face Eied in heaven?

36
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,720
Why don't you avoid heaven?

37
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,800
It's not the only place you can go.

38
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,080
- Watch it.
- No.

39
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:35,120
You're telling me I'm going to hell.

40
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,640
I'm not saying that.

41
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:39,280
Well, there are only heaven and hell.

42
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:43,160
Gosh, I thought Kratin was naughty,

43
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:46,560
but she can't compete with Cheewan.

44
00:04:46,640 --> 00:04:47,800
I agree, ma'am.

45
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,680
It's not true, Jaew.

46
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,520
It is.

47
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:56,960
Anyone who gets Poncheewa

48
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:01,320
as their in-law is lucky
as she's a good girl.

49
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:06,200
Hey, continue trying to get
Poncheewa and Saruj together.

50
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:07,840
Sure, ma'am.

51
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:11,800
And since you're going
to take care of Saruj,

52
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:15,880
I need you to take care
of another thing for me.

53
00:05:19,120 --> 00:05:21,920
Go!

54
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,400
Go!

55
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,280
Go!

56
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,280
Go!

57
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,120
- Gosh.
- What is this?

58
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:46,720
Why are you lazing around?

59
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,360
I just took a nap.

60
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:51,640
I've already done all the cleaning.

61
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:53,120
- Is that so?
- Yes.

62
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,840
Why is there still a layer of dust?

63
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:02,160
You were dreaming
about cockfighting, weren't you?

64
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,480
Yes.

65
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:04,960
Did you win?

66
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:08,160
Yes, but I woke up
before I got the prize money.

67
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:11,560
Prize money? Take this, you lazy ass.

68
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:14,680
M.R. Pavornruj and Mrs. Rasa
are away in America,

69
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:18,000
so you think
you can laze around, don't you?

70
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,440
Hey, from now on,

71
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:23,680
Ms. Cheewan will be taking care
of this house as ordered by Madam Orn.

72
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:26,520
If you laze around again,
I'll ask her to report you to Madam Orn.

73
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,560
Gosh.

74
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:29,000
You'd better watch out, Jon.

75
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,280
Get to work.

76
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,480
Let's help each other.

77
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,360
It's Mr. Saruj's house.

78
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:53,160
I'll make sure it's spotless.

79
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,680
It's finally done.

80
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,160
Hey,

81
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,560
my little one.

82
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,280
Switzerland.

83
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:40,120
I miss Switzerland so much.

84
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:43,240
Switzerland

85
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,680
is beautiful

86
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,640
and fragrant.

87
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:51,040
I miss it so much.

88
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:54,320
Do you only miss Switzerland?

89
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,600
What about the people there?

90
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,760
Do you miss them?

91
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:01,720
Well…

92
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,960
The people?

93
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:13,360
Of course.

94
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,640
Hey.

95
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,680
Wait.

96
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:29,080
Hey, that hurts.

97
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,520
Hey!

98
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,040
It's really you, Mr. Saruj!

99
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:34,080
It's really you.

100
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,720
I'm sorry.

101
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,320
I thought I was dreaming.

102
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,320
Dreaming?

103
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,880
What were you dreaming about?

104
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:47,880
Do you really miss someone?

105
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,120
Who do you miss?

106
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,840
I don't miss anyone.

107
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:58,680
And why are you here?

108
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:01,360
Aren't you supposed
to be working in Switzerland?

109
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,400
Gosh,

110
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:10,920
you're really back, my dear master.

111
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,040
Hello.

112
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:15,880
You didn't tell me you were coming.

113
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:18,840
I wouldn't have known
if they hadn't told me.

114
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,880
I didn't tell anyone I was coming back.

115
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,160
Who told you?

116
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:17,040
- Come here.
- How are you?

117
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:18,000
Gosh.

118
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,120
I miss you all so much!

119
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,520
The five monkeys are finally reunited!

120
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:33,080
Did you really think
you could keep it from us?

121
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,800
It's not that easy. We have an informant.

122
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,680
Welcome home, my dear cousin.

123
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,360
Congratulations on your new position,

124
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,120
Mr. Secretary to the Minister.

125
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:43,040
- Gosh.
- Thank you.

126
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:45,720
This means you'll be in Thailand
for a while, right?

127
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,080
Yes, I'll be here for a year
for the new position.

128
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,160
- Hey.
- Yes!

129
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:51,840
Why don't we party every weekend?

130
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:54,760
Let's do it!

131
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:57,480
- Party!
- Party!

132
00:12:57,560 --> 00:13:01,360
- Party!
- Party!

133
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:04,520
- Party!
- Party!

134
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:07,840
I miss you so much.

135
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:11,800
The people I wanted
to see the most are now here.

136
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,800
What a sweet talker you are.
Come, let's hug some more.

137
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:17,640
- Let's hug some more.
- I miss you!

138
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,680
Greetings, dear.

139
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:35,400
What is my name again?

140
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,240
Chatklao?

141
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:41,000
You're going to get this.

142
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,320
Saruj.

143
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:45,520
Come on, I remember all of you.

144
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,720
I'm just a little slow.

145
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,360
It was on the tip of my tongue.

146
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:56,720
Mr. Danai, my former boss back in England,

147
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:58,440
asked me to come back and help him.

148
00:13:58,520 --> 00:14:02,240
He wants you to work for him?
What kind of work is it?

149
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:05,280
Tomorrow, Mr. Danai will be appointed

150
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:07,560
Minister of Foreign Affairs

151
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,160
under the new government.

152
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:13,000
So what does this mean?

153
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:17,480
Mr. Saruj came back
to serve as the secretary to the minister.

154
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:20,920
That's fantastic, Madam Orn.

155
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,320
Hello, Madam Orn.

156
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,760
- Hello.
- Come here, dear.

157
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:35,960
Mr. Danai has been involved in politics
for a year now.

158
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,360
Once he made his way up,

159
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:40,960
he thought of Mr. Saruj,
his skillful mentee.

160
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:44,720
He wants someone who knows him well
to help him out.

161
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,480
I see.

162
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:49,560
And who are you?

163
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:52,960
Madam Orn.

164
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:55,280
I'm Lady Veena,

165
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:57,880
the wife of Permanent Secretary Narong.

166
00:14:57,960 --> 00:15:00,720
I come to greet you every year.

167
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,560
Don't you remember me?

168
00:15:02,640 --> 00:15:03,600
Really?

169
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:06,880
Mr. Saruj.

170
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:10,600
We came here to congratulate you.

171
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,520
Thank you.

172
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:19,000
Madam Orn, this is Venus, my daughter.

173
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,960
She's also just returned from abroad,

174
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:24,880
but she'll only be here temporarily
because we're doing fine financially.

175
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,280
- Right?
- Yes, Mom.

176
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:30,240
Greetings, everyone.

177
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:35,000
Hey, Cheewan. Look at this.

178
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:45,680
Great job! You did it so well.

179
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,800
Are you two friends?

180
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,600
We studied together in Switzerland.

181
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,960
But they're not that close.

182
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:56,800
Venus is closer to Mr. Saruj.

183
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:59,920
She became his favorite

184
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,560
when they were in Switzerland.

185
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:06,200
Mr. Saruj,

186
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,240
if you assume
a high-ranking position in the future,

187
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:11,400
please don't forget
Permanent Secretary Narong and Venus.

188
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:13,080
Please look after them.

189
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,040
Yes, ma'am.

190
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:34,320
I haven't been here for so long.

191
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,280
It's a bit run down.

192
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:43,320
My parents are away
doing charity work with the UN.

193
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,640
They have a house in America.

194
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:48,040
No one has been staying here.

195
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,360
As for me,

196
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:52,360
I didn't plan to return home,

197
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:54,160
so I didn't have it fixed up.

198
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:58,200
It's not your duty to do that.

199
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,880
You're their servant.

200
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:04,040
It's your job.

201
00:17:04,119 --> 00:17:06,319
You should have done it, Cheewan.

202
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,400
Madam Orn told you to clean it
a few days ago.

203
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:11,800
Are you still not done?

204
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:16,200
Actually, I just arrived yesterday,

205
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:18,040
- so--
- Don't argue with me.

206
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,720
Venus and I will take care of this.

207
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:27,319
We'll make sure
your servant isn't slacking off.

208
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:33,240
Why are you still here?
Go and clean up now.

209
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:37,240
You always need me to scold you
before you do anything.

210
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,200
Yes, ma'am.

211
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,600
Venus, go and keep an eye on her.

212
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:44,640
Sure.

213
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:51,200
Venus wants to help you with this.

214
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:54,680
You're a poor bachelor living alone.

215
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:08,320
Hey, Cheewan,
I'm going to test your English,

216
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,320
- so you won't forget it.
- Okay.

217
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,320
What do you call the thing
you use for storage?

218
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:13,680
Box.

219
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,000
And what happens when you repeat it?

220
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:18,040
Then it's…

221
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,480
Does that work?

222
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:24,160
Stop it right now.

223
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:25,560
Both of you.

224
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:30,000
Venus, I asked you to supervise her,

225
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:31,480
so do it.

226
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:33,920
Yes, Mom. Fuck!

227
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,440
I'm sorry.

228
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:41,200
Cheewan, you're messing with me.

229
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:43,600
That's enough, Cheewan.

230
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:46,720
I was already planning to get someone
to repair my house.

231
00:18:48,840 --> 00:18:49,760
Okay.

232
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:53,720
Were you already planning
to get someone to repair your house?

233
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,360
Leave this to me.

234
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:56,760
I know a contractor.

235
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:58,440
They're an acquaintance.

236
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:02,160
Okay.

237
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:12,200
Here, hold it.

238
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:14,480
Wait a second.

239
00:19:17,280 --> 00:19:18,640
Try to press it.

240
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:20,640
Hello,

241
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:25,120
I'd like to send a message to 644555.

242
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:28,280
Paper-thin rabbit, don't forget to eat.

243
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:30,720
Okay, thank you.

244
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,280
It's here.

245
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:40,880
PAPER-THIN RABBIT, DON'T FORGET TO EAT

246
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:42,960
- There it is.
- Look, honey.

247
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:45,040
- Yes.
- Gosh, "Paper-thin rabbit."

248
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,960
That's it. You only need

249
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,920
to remember the number, call the center,

250
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,600
and tell them your message.

251
00:19:50,680 --> 00:19:52,440
It's so easy.

252
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:54,360
Here you go, dear.

253
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:55,920
Take it.

254
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:56,920
Keep it with you.

255
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,920
- Try it out.
- Carry it with you.

256
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,080
Hey, Cheewa.

257
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:08,720
Teenagers keep it here.

258
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:11,560
Does she look cool?

259
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,720
Let me see.

260
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:16,520
- Look at you. You look so cool.
- Gosh.

261
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,680
You look so cool.

262
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:23,080
Now they can send messages
to their favorite child all day.

263
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,920
We're no longer needed.

264
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:28,120
Come on.

265
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:30,480
How could you think that?

266
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:34,400
Did you need to say that?

267
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:35,520
No, Mom.

268
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,000
Watch it.

269
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:44,880
Cheewa, is something wrong?

270
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:48,600
It's nothing.

271
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:27,240
Dad, Mom, I'm going to stay
with Cheewan for a while.

272
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:31,720
Why? Stay here with us.

