Hey, think carefully.

548
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:05,400
If Mr. Nava becomes prime minister,

549
00:43:05,480 --> 00:43:09,480
Mrs. Muslin will be the first lady.

550
00:43:09,560 --> 00:43:14,520
Do you think she'd be stupid enough
to get back together with Mr. Saruj?

551
00:43:14,600 --> 00:43:16,560
There's no way.

552
00:43:16,640 --> 00:43:20,840
You just need to get as close
to Mr. Saruj as you can.

553
00:43:20,920 --> 00:43:23,040
Just do what I say.

554
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:24,960
Listen.

555
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:29,240
Mr. Saruj is both handsome and rich.

556
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:32,920
Don't you want him?

557
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:52,600
I miss your mom.
I haven't talked to her for a while.

558
00:43:52,680 --> 00:43:54,520
There was a time

559
00:43:54,600 --> 00:43:56,800
when I came here to learn
the violin with her.

560
00:43:56,880 --> 00:43:58,200
Do you remember that?

561
00:43:58,280 --> 00:44:00,080
Yes, I do.

562
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:08,320
Well,

563
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:10,760
I'll go get more tea.

564
00:44:30,360 --> 00:44:32,840
There he is. Mr. Saruj is over there.

565
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:40,720
Hey, Mrs. Muslin is following him.

566
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:43,400
Saruj.

567
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:52,880
We haven't seen each other for a year.

568
00:44:52,960 --> 00:44:54,720
Is it a bit awkward?

569
00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:58,280
Actually, I should have asked you
before I came.

570
00:44:58,360 --> 00:44:59,920
But you didn't.

571
00:45:03,480 --> 00:45:06,760
They're alone together.

572
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:10,720
I must complete my mission
to get 500 baht.

573
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:11,920
Let's do it now.

574
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:13,560
Hold on, Jon.

575
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:17,400
Let's observe them for now.
They might just be talking.

576
00:45:18,720 --> 00:45:22,200
Madam Orn wants me to get in between them.
What do I do, Cheewan?

577
00:45:22,280 --> 00:45:24,280
Right. How are we going to do that?

578
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:26,640
Should I put myself
in between them physically?

579
00:45:26,720 --> 00:45:28,760
Mr. Saruj isn't stupid.

580
00:45:29,960 --> 00:45:33,720
When Lady Veena told me
you were moving back to Bangkok,

581
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:35,400
I was happy.

582
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:37,080
I miss you.

583
00:45:37,160 --> 00:45:39,040
You miss me?

584
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:42,000
How can you say that?

585
00:45:47,320 --> 00:45:50,120
Hey, I know now.

586
00:45:50,200 --> 00:45:53,920
Do you see that tree? I'll hit
the ant's nest and make it fall on her.

587
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,080
That'll definitely get them out of there.

588
00:45:56,160 --> 00:45:58,440
- Let me do it now.
- Hey, hold on.

589
00:45:58,520 --> 00:46:00,320
Don't be so hasty.

590
00:46:05,880 --> 00:46:09,280
Well, I assumed

591
00:46:09,360 --> 00:46:12,200
that you'd be happy to see me.

592
00:46:13,520 --> 00:46:15,200
But it doesn't seem to be that way.

593
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:20,600
Are you still mad at me?

594
00:46:20,680 --> 00:46:23,760
You chose what was best for you.

595
00:46:23,840 --> 00:46:25,480
You didn't do anything wrong.

596
00:46:28,680 --> 00:46:30,400
What was best for me?

597
00:46:32,960 --> 00:46:35,720
That hurts

598
00:46:35,800 --> 00:46:37,120
because it's not true.

599
00:46:38,200 --> 00:46:40,840
I used to think that it was for the best.

600
00:46:43,200 --> 00:46:44,880
But I was wrong.

601
00:46:46,040 --> 00:46:48,200
It was the worst thing I could have done.

602
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:57,920
Gosh, she's crying.

603
00:46:58,000 --> 00:47:00,160
Hey, trust me.

604
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:03,240
Men can't say no to a woman
when she cries.

605
00:47:03,320 --> 00:47:06,680
Hey, I have to stop him now.

606
00:47:06,760 --> 00:47:08,320
- Hey, Jon.
- Hey.

607
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:10,920
Gosh.

608
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:15,080
I'm sure Mr. Saruj won't give in to her.

609
00:47:15,160 --> 00:47:17,560
Hey, but she hasn't stopped crying.

610
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:21,400
Shouldn't she be happy?
She's married to a billionaire.

611
00:47:21,480 --> 00:47:24,120
Should I get in their way now?

612
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:25,680
What should I say?

613
00:47:25,760 --> 00:47:27,400
No, not yet.

614
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:32,280
Mr. Saruj will be able to handle it.
Trust me.

615
00:47:44,040 --> 00:47:46,720
Gosh, they're holding hands, Cheewan.

616
00:47:46,800 --> 00:47:49,560
Gosh, this woman.

617
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:55,800
It's okay.
Mr. Saruj will push her hands away.

618
00:47:55,880 --> 00:47:59,320
She's going to get a talking-to.

619
00:48:06,400 --> 00:48:07,360
I was wrong

620
00:48:08,320 --> 00:48:09,640
for leaving you.

621
00:48:15,240 --> 00:48:16,240
Mus.

622
00:48:24,240 --> 00:48:27,040
Let go of her hands now. Do it.

623
00:48:28,520 --> 00:48:29,840
Isn't he letting go?

624
00:48:32,600 --> 00:48:34,240
I'm not sure now.

625
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:36,280
- Mr. Saruj!
- Cheewan.

626
00:48:36,840 --> 00:48:40,240
Gosh, I'm going to get 500 baht.

627
00:48:43,520 --> 00:48:44,600
Mr. Saruj!

628
00:48:49,720 --> 00:48:51,840
The thing is…

629
00:48:52,840 --> 00:48:56,320
I have a question about Thai manners.

630
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:58,640
My teacher asked,

631
00:48:58,720 --> 00:49:00,720
is it appropriate for a married woman

632
00:49:00,800 --> 00:49:03,720
to hold hands
with her ex-boyfriend in a private place?

633
00:49:05,120 --> 00:49:07,760
Who are you?

634
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:10,760
I'm Cheewan, Madam Orn's servant.

635
00:49:15,840 --> 00:49:18,840
Poncheewa, come here.

636
00:49:35,560 --> 00:49:37,160
Were you two spying on us?

637
00:49:38,760 --> 00:49:41,800
What should I tell
my teacher, Mrs. Muslin?

638
00:49:42,880 --> 00:49:44,160
Cheewan.

639
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:47,240
I'm going to ask you a question
about manners too.

640
00:49:47,320 --> 00:49:48,760
Is it right

641
00:49:48,840 --> 00:49:50,320
to spy on others

642
00:49:50,400 --> 00:49:51,600
and meddle in their business?

643
00:49:52,360 --> 00:49:54,560
You have no right to ask me that.

644
00:49:54,640 --> 00:49:56,440
And why are you angry at me?

645
00:49:56,520 --> 00:49:57,560
Cheewan.

646
00:50:03,440 --> 00:50:05,400
- Mus.
- Gosh, it's ants.

647
00:50:05,480 --> 00:50:07,520
Mus.

648
00:50:07,600 --> 00:50:08,960
Let me help you.

649
00:50:12,160 --> 00:50:14,040
Jon, what are you doing?

650
00:50:14,120 --> 00:50:16,400
Well, I…

651
00:50:16,480 --> 00:50:20,040
You were talking about Thai manners.
Now, let's talk about agriculture.

652
00:50:20,120 --> 00:50:21,880
I wanted to cut this branch,

653
00:50:21,960 --> 00:50:24,160
but I didn't see the ant's nest.

654
00:50:24,240 --> 00:50:25,600
I really didn't see it.

655
00:50:26,600 --> 00:50:27,880
Mr. Saruj.

656
00:50:27,960 --> 00:50:30,840
You can't touch a married woman like that.

657
00:50:30,920 --> 00:50:33,000
Take your hands off her.

658
00:50:33,080 --> 00:50:35,320
Stop it.
You have no right to order me around

659
00:50:35,400 --> 00:50:37,320
or meddle in my private business.

660
00:50:39,360 --> 00:50:43,160
You and Jon have gone too far.

661
00:50:45,640 --> 00:50:48,400
Let's go inside so you can take a shower.

662
00:50:48,480 --> 00:50:49,440
Okay.

663
00:50:53,680 --> 00:50:55,680
Did you have to scold me?

664
00:50:56,720 --> 00:50:58,240
Fine.

665
00:50:59,800 --> 00:51:01,080
Cheewan.

666
00:51:08,880 --> 00:51:10,920
Take a shower and wash your hair.

667
00:51:11,000 --> 00:51:12,560
I'll go and find some clothes for you.

668
00:51:13,160 --> 00:51:14,240
Okay.

669
00:51:41,480 --> 00:51:43,600
We're worried about you.

670
00:51:44,160 --> 00:51:46,240
Mrs. Muslin's husband is a gangster.

671
00:51:46,320 --> 00:51:49,440
Nat is a thug,
but I'm sure his dad is worse.

672
00:51:49,520 --> 00:51:51,360
Aren't you afraid he'll get back at you

673
00:51:51,440 --> 00:51:53,360
for having an affair with his wife?

674
00:51:53,440 --> 00:51:55,400
That's nonsense. What affair?

675
00:51:55,480 --> 00:51:56,720
We were just talking.

676
00:51:56,800 --> 00:51:58,320
But you were holding hands.

677
00:51:58,400 --> 00:52:00,000
We may not be a couple anymore,

678
00:52:00,080 --> 00:52:01,880
but she's still my friend.

679
00:52:02,440 --> 00:52:03,760
The word friend,

680
00:52:03,840 --> 00:52:05,040
do you know what it means?

681
00:52:05,120 --> 00:52:08,080
Can you really be friends with her

682
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:09,760
when she hurt you?

683
00:52:09,840 --> 00:52:10,880
She ditched you.

684
00:52:10,960 --> 00:52:13,120
Yes, she ditched me.

685
00:52:13,200 --> 00:52:15,280
She hurt me.

686
00:52:15,360 --> 00:52:17,200
I'm well aware of that.

687
00:52:17,280 --> 00:52:18,680
I don't need anyone to tell me

688
00:52:18,760 --> 00:52:21,440
and repeat it right to my face.

689
00:52:22,160 --> 00:52:23,920
I want to get hurt,

690
00:52:24,000 --> 00:52:25,520
I want to get ditched,

691
00:52:25,600 --> 00:52:28,200
I want to deal with this by myself.

692
00:52:28,280 --> 00:52:29,960
You have no right to stick your nose in.

693
00:52:36,760 --> 00:52:37,920
You're right.

694
00:52:39,680 --> 00:52:41,760
I don't have the right to get involved.

695
00:52:41,840 --> 00:52:43,360
I don't have the right to mean well.

696
00:52:46,080 --> 00:52:47,680
I'm just a servant.

697
00:52:49,920 --> 00:52:51,320
I'm just a servant.

698
00:52:51,400 --> 00:52:55,040
Don't pretend I'm your friend
if this is all it takes to make you mad.

699
00:52:55,120 --> 00:52:57,480
You probably don't regard me
as your friend.

700
00:52:58,160 --> 00:52:59,840
I'm just a servant to you.

701
00:53:01,680 --> 00:53:03,040
That's how it should be.

702
00:53:58,120 --> 00:53:59,360
Cheewan.

703
00:54:00,200 --> 00:54:01,960
Why are you crying?

704
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:07,640
Why are you crying, Cheewan?

705
00:54:08,960 --> 00:54:11,680
Can't he tell that I only meant well?

706
00:54:13,320 --> 00:54:17,120
Did he have to scold me like that?

707
00:54:18,440 --> 00:54:21,480
- He's so mean.
- Don't do this.

708
00:54:23,440 --> 00:54:24,680
There, there.

709
00:54:30,720 --> 00:54:31,880
She ditched you.

710
00:54:31,960 --> 00:54:34,120
Yes, she ditched me.

711
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:36,160
She hurt me.

712
00:54:36,240 --> 00:54:38,200
I'm well aware of that.

713
00:54:38,280 --> 00:54:39,680
I don't need anyone to tell me.

714
00:54:39,760 --> 00:54:42,120
I want to deal with this by myself.

715
00:54:42,200 --> 00:54:43,880
You have no right to stick your nose in.

716
00:54:47,160 --> 00:54:48,680
He's so mean.

717
00:54:50,040 --> 00:54:52,800
He's just so mean.

718
00:55:10,080 --> 00:55:11,560
Is it still itchy?

719
00:55:12,040 --> 00:55:13,080
Have you applied some balm?

720
00:55:14,400 --> 00:55:16,960
There's one on my neck I can't reach.

721
00:55:17,040 --> 00:55:17,960
Let me help you.

722
00:55:30,440 --> 00:55:32,880
I'm sorry for what they did.

723
00:55:32,960 --> 00:55:35,160
They're not normally like that.

724
00:55:37,080 --> 00:55:38,920
That girl…

725
00:55:42,720 --> 00:55:44,440
Cheewan.

726
00:55:44,520 --> 00:55:46,240
She's the daughter of Mom Kratin.

727
00:55:46,320 --> 00:55:49,600
The other one is Poncheewa.

728
00:55:50,520 --> 00:55:52,480
She's Mrs. Kedsara's daughter.

729
00:55:54,880 --> 00:55:58,480
Jon, you're supposed to keep them apart,

730
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:01,040
but you have put them closer.

731
00:56:01,120 --> 00:56:02,760
You won't get the 500 baht anymore.

732
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:04,960
Oh no.

733
00:56:06,560 --> 00:56:08,800
That was a smart question

734
00:56:08,880 --> 00:56:11,200
about whether a married woman
should be doing that.

735
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:14,560
I should have felt ashamed.

736
00:56:15,120 --> 00:56:18,760
I deserve to be insulted by her.

737
00:56:30,640 --> 00:56:32,360
What's going on with you?

738
00:56:33,080 --> 00:56:34,880
You said things aren't going well.

739
00:56:44,720 --> 00:56:46,880
Nava cheated on me.

740
00:56:46,960 --> 00:56:50,000
Someone saw him take a woman to a hotel,

741
00:56:50,080 --> 00:56:53,520
even after he promised me
that I was the only one for him.

742
00:56:54,120 --> 00:56:55,800
Did you ask him about it?

743
00:56:55,880 --> 00:56:58,120
He said it was just a fling

744
00:56:58,200 --> 00:57:01,200
and that he wasn't serious about her.

745
00:57:01,800 --> 00:57:04,080
He said I was being petty

746
00:57:04,160 --> 00:57:07,120
and that my expectations
of him were too high.

747
00:57:07,720 --> 00:57:09,640
I tried to get over it.

748
00:57:09,720 --> 00:57:12,280
I worked to make myself forget about it.

749
00:57:13,520 --> 00:57:15,240
So you went back to work.

750
00:57:17,840 --> 00:57:18,920
That's right.

751
00:57:22,760 --> 00:57:24,680
Please let me renovate your house.

752
00:57:28,960 --> 00:57:30,280
Please don't chase me away.

753
00:57:30,360 --> 00:57:33,280
I'll go mad if I have to stay home.

754
00:58:25,720 --> 00:58:28,560
You're right.
I don't have the right to get involved.

755
00:58:28,640 --> 00:58:30,440
I don't have the right to mean well.

756
00:58:31,000 --> 00:58:32,600
I'm just a servant.

757
00:58:33,160 --> 00:58:36,320
Don't pretend I'm your friend
if this is all it takes to make you mad.

758
00:58:36,400 --> 00:58:38,640
You probably don't regard me
as your friend.

759
00:59:19,280 --> 00:59:22,360
About yesterday, I want to…

760
00:59:26,440 --> 00:59:28,920
Muslin and I have known each other
for over ten years.

761
00:59:29,560 --> 00:59:31,400
Even though we have broken up,

762
00:59:31,480 --> 00:59:35,080
I still consider her a friend,
and I was worried about her.

763
00:59:35,560 --> 00:59:38,480
You and Poncheewa are close.

764
00:59:38,560 --> 00:59:39,720
I'm sure you've argued,

765
00:59:39,800 --> 00:59:41,560
but you still care
about each other, right?

766
00:59:43,280 --> 00:59:45,280
The same goes for me and Muslin.

767
00:59:48,600 --> 00:59:49,520
Cheewan.

768
00:59:54,320 --> 00:59:56,920
You're back, Mr. Saruj.

769
00:59:59,520 --> 01:00:00,480
Well…

770
01:00:01,840 --> 01:00:03,480
Did the girls come here?

771
01:00:03,560 --> 01:00:05,520
No, sir.

772
01:00:05,600 --> 01:00:08,200
They went to enroll
at Ramkhamhaeng University.

773
01:00:08,280 --> 01:00:11,160
They asked me to tell you
that they won't come here anymore

774
01:00:11,240 --> 01:00:12,640
because they have to focus
on their studies.

775
01:00:14,960 --> 01:00:17,760
Mr. Saruj, Ms. Venus made you some food.

776
01:00:17,840 --> 01:00:19,480
She wanted to eat with you,

777
01:00:19,560 --> 01:00:21,600
but she couldn't wait and left.

778
01:00:21,680 --> 01:00:23,120
Do you want me to heat up the food?

779
01:00:25,880 --> 01:00:27,240
I'll go lock the gate then.

780
01:00:49,920 --> 01:00:51,240
It's waist-high.

781
01:00:58,040 --> 01:01:00,120
There you go.

782
01:01:00,200 --> 01:01:01,160
Chest-high.

783
01:01:01,720 --> 01:01:02,760
Chest-high.

784
01:01:05,120 --> 01:01:06,040
Ms. Cheewan.

785
01:01:06,680 --> 01:01:07,520
Yes?

786
01:01:07,600 --> 01:01:11,160
Mr. Saruj can't find his notebook.

787
01:01:11,240 --> 01:01:13,360
He said you cleaned his room,

788
01:01:13,440 --> 01:01:15,920
so he wants you to help him look for it.

789
01:01:16,880 --> 01:01:18,320
Which notebook?

790
01:01:18,400 --> 01:01:20,560
Well…

791
01:01:20,640 --> 01:01:22,800
I don't know.
I think you should talk to him.

792
01:01:22,880 --> 01:01:24,120
He's waiting.

793
01:01:26,160 --> 01:01:30,120
I'm not free. I'm busy playing this now.

794
01:01:30,200 --> 01:01:31,200
What?

795
01:01:31,280 --> 01:01:33,240
- Look at this, Jon.
- Okay.

796
01:01:33,320 --> 01:01:35,640
My gosh, you're so good.

797
01:01:35,720 --> 01:01:37,200
Come on, Jon. Try it.

798
01:01:37,280 --> 01:01:38,480
Me?

799
01:01:38,560 --> 01:01:39,640
Yes. Come on.

800
01:01:39,720 --> 01:01:41,280
- All right.
- Come on.

801
01:01:41,360 --> 01:01:43,800
Jon.

802
01:01:43,880 --> 01:01:45,360
- Jon.
- Jon.

803
01:01:45,440 --> 01:01:47,400
My gosh.

804
01:01:47,960 --> 01:01:49,280
Please lower it.

805
01:01:52,240 --> 01:01:54,000
A bit more.

806
01:01:54,080 --> 01:01:55,640
Come on, Jon.

807
01:01:55,720 --> 01:01:57,160
Some more.

808
01:02:02,680 --> 01:02:03,800
Am I good?

809
01:02:03,880 --> 01:02:06,520
Awesome, but the jump was so unnecessary.

810
01:02:09,640 --> 01:02:11,760
That's it.

811
01:02:11,840 --> 01:02:13,320
Where are you going?

812
01:02:13,400 --> 01:02:15,080
We need to find the notebook.

813
01:02:15,800 --> 01:02:18,960
I'm not going. Let's continue.
We're up to ear level now.

814
01:02:19,040 --> 01:02:19,960
Ear level.

815
01:02:21,120 --> 01:02:22,320
Come on.

816
01:02:45,720 --> 01:02:47,680
Mr. Saruj said he wanted to have lon puu.

817
01:02:47,760 --> 01:02:48,600
Can you make it?

818
01:02:48,680 --> 01:02:49,840
He's waiting at his house.

819
01:02:51,720 --> 01:02:54,760
I'm not free.
I'm making soup for Madam Orn.

820
01:02:56,320 --> 01:02:57,280
Okay.

821
01:03:09,640 --> 01:03:10,560
Ms. Cheewan.

822
01:03:12,240 --> 01:03:13,160
Ms. Cheewan.

823
01:03:13,840 --> 01:03:16,640
Mr. Saruj needs to talk to you
about an important matter.

824
01:03:16,720 --> 01:03:17,920
I'm not free.

825
01:03:18,560 --> 01:03:19,400
What are you doing?

826
01:03:19,480 --> 01:03:20,600
I'm chilling out.

827
01:03:22,080 --> 01:03:23,160
Okay.

828
01:04:19,720 --> 01:04:21,000
I'm a bad person.

829
01:04:22,200 --> 01:04:23,960
I'm a bad person.

830
01:04:25,200 --> 01:04:27,800
I've let my parents down.

831
01:04:42,960 --> 01:04:45,040
I'm in Thailand.

832
01:04:45,120 --> 01:04:47,680
I miss you so much. I'll go see you.

833
01:05:14,000 --> 01:05:16,160
Gosh, it's a Tamagotchi.

834
01:05:19,480 --> 01:05:21,120
"For Cheewan."

835
01:05:22,440 --> 01:05:23,360
For me?

836
01:05:26,360 --> 01:05:28,360
I wonder who it's from.

837
01:05:35,120 --> 01:05:37,040
Come on.

838
01:05:37,120 --> 01:05:40,360
Hey, Tamagotchi. Come here.

839
01:05:41,160 --> 01:05:45,080
Where are you going? Come back.

840
01:05:51,800 --> 01:05:53,600
Tamagotchi.

841
01:05:55,200 --> 01:05:56,560
Gosh, you.

842
01:06:00,800 --> 01:06:01,880
Fine.

843
01:06:21,160 --> 01:06:22,720
It's for you.

844
01:06:25,800 --> 01:06:27,120
Who says I want it?

845
01:06:27,200 --> 01:06:31,160
If I hadn't lured you with a toy,
then I wouldn't get to see you.

846
01:06:33,320 --> 01:06:35,640
I said I don't want it.

847
01:06:35,720 --> 01:06:37,640
I just wanted to look at it.

848
01:06:37,720 --> 01:06:39,840
Are you still mad at me?

849
01:06:39,920 --> 01:06:41,960
You were also wrong

850
01:06:42,040 --> 01:06:44,160
for meddling in my business.

851
01:06:44,240 --> 01:06:45,680
If you want me to apologize,

852
01:06:45,760 --> 01:06:48,440
you must promise me not to do it again.

853
01:06:49,840 --> 01:06:50,960
She ditched you.

854
01:06:51,040 --> 01:06:53,320
Yes, she ditched me.

855
01:06:53,880 --> 01:06:55,480
She hurt me.

856
01:06:55,560 --> 01:06:57,400
I'm well aware of that.

857
01:06:57,480 --> 01:06:58,880
I don't need anyone to tell me.

858
01:06:58,960 --> 01:07:01,480
I want to deal with this by myself.

859
01:07:01,560 --> 01:07:03,360
You have no right to stick your nose in.

860
01:07:08,360 --> 01:07:11,400
Yes, I shouldn't have said that.

861
01:07:13,200 --> 01:07:16,080
Do you admit now that it was also wrong

862
01:07:16,160 --> 01:07:18,160
to meddle in my private matters?

863
01:07:20,360 --> 01:07:21,400
Yes,

864
01:07:21,480 --> 01:07:23,520
I won't do that again.

865
01:07:23,600 --> 01:07:25,240
In that case, I'm sorry

866
01:07:25,320 --> 01:07:27,040
if I was too harsh.

867
01:07:36,120 --> 01:07:40,720
How about this? To make up for it,
will you take me to Siam?

868
01:07:40,800 --> 01:07:42,360
Let's go to Siam.

869
01:07:42,440 --> 01:07:43,880
Sure,

870
01:07:43,960 --> 01:07:45,560
I haven't been there for ages.

871
01:07:47,160 --> 01:07:48,600
Are you asking me out?

872
01:07:49,920 --> 01:07:51,920
Westerners call it…

873
01:07:52,000 --> 01:07:53,200
It's not a date.

874
01:07:53,280 --> 01:07:54,960
Poncheewa is coming too.

875
01:07:57,520 --> 01:07:58,520
Fine, let's go.

876
01:07:59,880 --> 01:08:02,040
Since we're going to Siam,

877
01:08:02,120 --> 01:08:03,400
I guess you don't want this anymore.

878
01:08:05,160 --> 01:08:06,360
Thank you.

879
01:08:08,400 --> 01:08:09,800
Tamagotchi.

880
01:08:35,680 --> 01:08:38,120
I know a good contractor.

881
01:08:39,720 --> 01:08:41,520
Why did you cut in front of me?

882
01:08:42,080 --> 01:08:42,960
Ma'am.

883
01:08:44,120 --> 01:08:45,439
This isn't wine.

884
01:08:45,520 --> 01:08:47,160
It's called budu.

885
01:08:48,240 --> 01:08:50,960
I have a plan to get them together.

886
01:08:51,040 --> 01:08:52,960
- Really?
- What's the plan?

887
01:08:53,040 --> 01:08:55,800
I have to oversee the renovation
of the house in Khao Yai?

888
01:08:58,000 --> 01:08:59,000
Are you okay?

889
01:09:01,960 --> 01:09:03,200
Gosh.

890
01:09:03,279 --> 01:09:05,479
Did you kiss my cheek?

891
01:09:06,439 --> 01:09:07,960
When you hug the one you love,

892
01:09:08,040 --> 01:09:10,000
a warmth radiates from them.

893
01:09:10,080 --> 01:09:11,720
It's not like when you hug someone else.

894
01:09:12,200 --> 01:09:14,319
Whose hug is warmer,

895
01:09:14,399 --> 01:09:16,120
Muslin's or Cheewan's?

896
